&lt;h3&gt;Erev Shavuot&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Notes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To reaffirm our people&#039;s acceptance of Torah on Shavuot, many have the custom of studying Torah through the night.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Candlelighting&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Before dark, light candles. Recite the festival candle blessing and shehecheyanu (MT 384).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Ma&#039;ariv&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival evening service (MT 384).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival Amidah with appropriate additions for Shavuot (MT 468).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;During Dinner&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recite festival evening Kiddush (MT 386).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Many have the custom of eating dairy meals on Shavuot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Add Ya&#039;aleh v&#039;Yavo for Shavuot and Harachaman for Yom Tov to Birkat Hamazon&lt;/p&gt;
